        "version_id": "CUNP",
        "version_name": "和合本新標點（神版）",
        "lang": "cht",
        "text": "王就甚憂愁；但因他所起的誓，又因同席的人，就不肯推辭，"
      },
      "nasb": {
        "version_id": "NASB",
        "version_name": "New American Standard Bible",
        "lang": "en",
        "text": "And although the king was very sorry, yet because of his oaths and because of his dinner guests, he was unwilling to refuse her."
      },
      "niv": {
        "version_id": "NIV",
        "version_name": "New International Version",
        "lang": "en",
        "text": "The king was greatly distressed, but because of his oaths and his dinner guests, he did not want to refuse her."
      },
      "nlt": {
        "version_id": "NLT",
        "version_name": "New Living Translation",
        "lang": "en",
        "text": "Then the king deeply regretted what he had said; but because of the vows he had made in front of his guests, he couldn’t refuse her."
      }
